page.title: 04CHURCH OF WYTHICOMBE
page.content: The parish church of Wythicombe named St Nicolas.Was built out of rubble and lime wash. 1.The Sanctuary, was dated back to the year 1230. 2.The Font,is dated back to 1180. 3.The Tower,is 40ft high and was renewed in 1903. 4.The Bells, in the tower are also dated 1903. 5.The Porch,below the belfry is dated 1000 years old. 6.The Grave stones in the church yard are dated, A.Elizabeth Gay died 1926. B.John Sully died 1900. C.Charlotte Sully died 1881. D.Earnest Case died 1887. E.Anne Grithin died 1836. 7.West street was built in the year 1624. ---------------
